;s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:13;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WebDevStudios";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:14;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"WebDevStudios.com";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8068";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:411:"This year at WordCamp St. Louis, Brian Messenlehner will be speaking, Sarah Pressler will be volunteering, and Cristina Cannon will be in attendance! WordCamp St. Louis is being held on March, 1st 2014 at the Danforth Campus of Washington University &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/24/wds-at-wordcamp-st-louis-2014/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2878:"<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/st-louis.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-8069" alt="st louis" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/st-louis-1024x180.png" width="640" height="112" /></a>This year at <a href="http://2014.stlouis.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp St. Louis</a>, <a title="Brian Messenlehner" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-messenlehner/">Brian Messenlehner</a> will be speaking, <a title="Sarah Pressler" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/sarah-pressler/">Sarah Pressler</a> will be volunteering, and <a title="Cristina Cannon" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/cristina-cannon/">Cristina Cannon</a> will be in attendance! WordCamp St. Louis is being held on <strong>March, 1st 2014</strong> at the Danforth Campus of <a href="http://wustl.edu">Washington University</a> in the <a href="http://wustl.edu/community/visitors/tour/danforth/laboratory-sciences-building.html">Laboratory Sciences Building.</a> You can find Sarah handing out badges and t-shirts and at the <a href="http://2014.stlouis.wordcamp.org/happiness-bar/">Happiness Bar</a> for beginners, while Cristina will be hanging around filling her brain with awesome WordPress knowledge. As for Brian, you can listen to him speak his knowledge about <span style="text-decoration: underline">WordPress as an Application Framework (Intermediate)</span>. You can find Brian in the <strong>User II track at 4:00 PM CST</strong>.</p>\n<p>A description of Brian&#8217;s talk:</p>\n<blockquote><p>Despite starting out as a blogging platform and currently existing primarily as a content management system, WordPress is powerful enough and flexible enough to run any type of web application including hybrid mobile apps. Whether you’re a novice WordPress user or an experienced web developer you can leverage WordPress in many non-traditional ways. We will go over how to rapidly build scalable and secure applications and how to save time and money doing so. We will also showcase some really cool applications and examples of building things with WordPress while thinking out of the box.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Along with presenting and volunteering, WebDevStudios is <a href="http://2014.stlouis.wordcamp.org/sponsors/">sponsoring</a> WordCamp St. Louis this year! We love supporting the WordPress community, and sponsoring events is one of our favorite ways to show it!</p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t get the chance to speaking with Brian, Sarah, or Cristina during WordCamp hours, you can catch all three of them at the After Party that is happening directly after the WordCamp is over. Brian, Sarah, and Cristina are looking forward to reconnecting with those of you they&#8217;ve already had the pleasure of meeting, and are also excited to connect with those of you they haven&#8217;t!</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll see you there!</p>\n<div></div>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/24/wds-at-wordcamp-st-louis-2014/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"WDS Welcomes Stacy Kvernmo!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:63:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/10/wds-welcomes-stacy-kvernmo/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/10/wds-welcomes-stacy-kvernmo/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 10 Feb 2014 14:52:25 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Twitter";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8052";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:362:"We are very excited to welcome our newest member of the team, Stacy Kvernmo! Stacy comes on board as our newest Front End Designer and today is her first day at WebDev, so wish her well. Stacy has been a &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/10/wds-welcomes-stacy-kvernmo/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2246:"<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/stacy-headshot4.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-8053" alt="stacy-headshot4" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/stacy-headshot4-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /></a>We are very excited to welcome our newest member of the team, Stacy Kvernmo! Stacy comes on board as our newest Front End Designer and today is her first day at WebDev, so wish her well.</p>\n<p>Stacy has been a WordPress fanatic since 2009 and hasn&#8217;t built a site outside of WordPress since then (with the exception of a Drupal site that she was handed, and then rebuilt it in WordPress!). She has been freelancing full-time since 2009, is an active member of the Aurora WordPress Meetup Group and attends WordCamps every chance she gets.</p>\n<p>Stacy&#8217;s web design career began in 2002 at a small creative agency which focused on web design and video production. She was originally hired as a print designer, but they needed more help in web, so she began to do both. At the agency, Stacy was in charge of many aspects of designing a website including creating the initial concept, carrying it out in a visual design, converting PSDs to html/css and building out a full html website (at the time when her company didn&#8217;t use a CMS). As her skills began to develop, she found herself wanting to learn more. Stacy believes she is a kick ass designer. As she has grown in her profession she has realized she REALLY enjoys the actual development of the site and thinks the problem solving aspect is a fun challenge. She has worked hard to become an expert in both visual design and front-end development. By working in small agencies and then doing freelance, she found that you are forced to wear many hats and uses these skills to make great sites for her clients.</p>\n<p>When Stacy isn&#8217;t designing and creating sites in WordPress, she enjoys spending time with her beautiful family ( you can learn more about them on her web site at: <a href="http://www.kverica.com/">http://www.kverica.com/</a>) and doing yoga. You can also follow Stacy on Twitter &#8212; <a href="https://twitter.com/funstacy">@funstacy</a>.</p>\n<p>Welcome to the team, Stacy!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/10/wds-welcomes-stacy-kvernmo/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s: