(1511, 213, 'new_paragraph_4_new_content', 'The Edmonton Community Legal Centre''s mission is to provide effective advocacy and access to justice in a supportive environment to persons living with a low income.\r\n\r\nBrownlee LLP lawyers donate their time on a monthly basis to the Edmonton Community Legal Centre through a clinic comprised of 4 – 5 Brownlee lawyers. They provide legal information and advice on a variety of legal matters. Additionally, many lawyers at the firm donate their time individually to this cause.\r\n\r\nTo find out more about the ECLC please visit <a href="http://www.eclc.ca/">www.eclc.ca</a>.'),
(1512, 213, '_new_paragraph_4_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(1513, 213, 'new_paragraph_5_new_title', 'SUIT YOURSELF'),
(1514, 213, '_new_paragraph_5_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(1515, 213, 'new_paragraph_5_new_content', 'Suit Yourself is an initiative where low-income women re-entering the work force are provided with business attire for interviews. Women may receive suits, dresses, closed toed shoes and accessories which help them to achieve a professional appearance and develop the confidence required to attain a position in the work force. If hired, they are provided with a couple of additional outfits to help encourage long-term employment.\r\n\r\nThe Brownlee LLP family has donated an abundance of clothing, shoes and accessories to this worthwhile initiative to ensure that women have the resources to successfully move into the work force.'),
(1516, 213, '_new_paragraph_5_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(1517, 213, 'new_paragraph_6_new_title', 'CROSSROADS HOUSE'),
(1518, 213, '_new_paragraph_6_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(1519, 213, 'new_paragraph_6_new_content', 'Crossroads House is a service that provides housing and social support to approximately 18 women. These women have often left an abusive situation or life on the street and are trying to make a transition to a healthy, mainstream lifestyle.  Crossroads House provides women with a safe and welcoming environment to help them move confidently into an improved home situation. Women are also given access to counselling and are assisted with developing skills to ensure that a positive lifestyle can be maintained.\r\n\r\nBrownlee works every year to provide a Christmas hamper for every individual currently living in the house. These hampers will provide each woman with greatly needed toiletries and clothing that will aid her with her transition.'),
(1520, 213, '_new_paragraph_6_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(1521, 213, 'new_paragraph', '7'),
(1522, 213, '_new_paragraph', 'field_531d56646e418'),
(1523, 25, 'new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'Community Involvement'),
(1524, 25, '_new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(1525, 25, 'new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'Brownlee supports various local, regional, and national charities on an ongoing basis through sponsorships and donations; however our biggest collaboration is that of our fall United Way Campaign. Brownlee supports this cause annually and in 2013 made a total contribution of $60,177.50, our biggest single contribution yet! Our total funds raised are now at an astounding $512,800.50'),
(1526, 25, '_new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(1527, 25, 'new_paragraph_1_new_title', 'MAKE-A-WISH FOUNDATION'),
(1528, 25, '_new_paragraph_1_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(1529, 25, 'new_paragraph_1_new_content', 'The mission of Make-A-Wish® Canada is to grant the wishes of children with life-threatening medical conditions to enrich the human experience with hope, strength and joy.\r\n\r\nBrownlee LLP is committed to giving back to the community and is happy to announce our partnership with Make-A-Wish® which will support wish granting efforts in the province of Alberta. We will keep you posted on our "Wish Stories" as they develop and invite you to learn more about this foundation and get involved by visiting <a href="http://www.makeawish.ca/">www.makeawish.ca</a>.'),
(1530, 25, '_new_paragraph_1_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(1531, 25, 'new_paragraph_2_new_title', 'THE UNITED WAY'),
(1532, 25, '_new_paragraph_2_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(1533, 25, 'new_paragraph_2_new_content', 'With United Way it''s not about supporting one cause. They focus on the areas that need change the most, with contributions from our supporters becoming part of a major community-building effort. They bring together organizations, businesses, governments, community members, and more than 50 agency partners in the social services sector who care about the issues we face in the Alberta Capital Region. Together, they represent one of the most critical and extensive collaborative approaches for change. No other local community organization does this - it’s what makes United Way unique, and it helps create the greatest impact possible for our community. To learn more about the United Way and how you can get involved you can visit their website at <a href="http://www.myunitedway.ca/">www.myunitedway.ca</a>'),
(1534, 25, '_new_paragraph_2_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(1535, 25, 'new_paragraph_3_new_title', 'KIDS KOTTAGE FOUNDATION'),
(1536, 25, '_new_paragraph_3_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(1537, 25, 'new_paragraph_3_new_content', 'Kids Kottage is Edmonton’s first and only crisis nursery, opened in 1995 with a mandate to prevent child abuse and neglect before it comes a way of life.\r\n\r\nKids Kottage offers 24-hour service to parents who need their support. During a time of crisis, they keep children safe, and work with parents during and after their children’s stay with them – to help them strengthen their family and give their children and themselves a strong, safe and healthy environment.\r\n\r\nBrownlee LLP has enjoyed a long term relationship with the Kids Kottage to support this much needed organization in our community. Together, we create and distribute a yearly calendar that features artwork made by the children while at the “Kottage”.\r\n\r\nFurther, Brownlee LLP volunteered at the 19th Annual Radiothon 2012 hosted by 105.9 Shine FM that helped to raise a total of over $90,032.00 for the foundation in a single day!\r\n\r\nTo learn more about Kids Kottage and how you can help, you can view their website <a href="http://www.kidskottage.org/">www.kidskottage.org</a>or to request a copy of the Brownlee LLP/Kids Kottage 2013 desktop calendar, please contact Vicki Marak @<a href="mailto:vmarak@brownleelaw.com">vmarak@brownleelaw.com</a>'),
