(2282, 297, '_new_paragraph_3_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(2283, 297, 'new_paragraph_3_new_content', 'The Edmonton Community Legal Centre''s mission is to provide effective advocacy and access to justice in a supportive environment to persons living with a low income.\r\n\r\nBrownlee LLP lawyers donate their time on a monthly basis to the Edmonton Community Legal Centre through a clinic comprised of 4 – 5 Brownlee lawyers. They provide legal information and advice on a variety of legal matters. Additionally, many lawyers at the firm donate their time individually to this cause.\r\n\r\nTo find out more about the ECLC please visit <a href="http://www.eclc.ca/">www.eclc.ca</a>.'),
(2284, 297, '_new_paragraph_3_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(2285, 297, 'new_paragraph_4_new_title', 'Suit Yourself'),
(2286, 297, '_new_paragraph_4_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(2287, 297, 'new_paragraph_4_new_content', 'Suit Yourself is an initiative where low-income women re-entering the work force are provided with business attire for interviews. Women may receive suits, dresses, closed toed shoes and accessories which help them to achieve a professional appearance and develop the confidence required to attain a position in the work force. If hired, they are provided with a couple of additional outfits to help encourage long-term employment.\r\n\r\nThe Brownlee LLP family has donated an abundance of clothing, shoes and accessories to this worthwhile initiative to ensure that women have the resources to successfully move into the work force.'),
(2288, 297, '_new_paragraph_4_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(2289, 297, 'new_paragraph_5_new_title', 'Crossroads House'),
(2290, 297, '_new_paragraph_5_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(2291, 297, 'new_paragraph_5_new_content', 'Crossroads House is a service that provides housing and social support to approximately 18 women. These women have often left an abusive situation or life on the street and are trying to make a transition to a healthy, mainstream lifestyle.  Crossroads House provides women with a safe and welcoming environment to help them move confidently into an improved home situation. Women are also given access to counselling and are assisted with developing skills to ensure that a positive lifestyle can be maintained.\r\n\r\nBrownlee works every year to provide a Christmas hamper for every individual currently living in the house. These hampers will provide each woman with greatly needed toiletries and clothing that will aid her with her transition.'),
