(3610, 348, 'bio', '<div>\r\n\r\nBarry has been a general counsel to municipalities and municipal organizations for over 30 years. During that time, he has practiced in all major areas of municipal law: Municipal Governance &amp; Authority; Expropriation; Annexation and Amalgamation; Inter-Municipal Disputes; Land Use Planning; Utilities Regulation and Franchise Agreements; Telecommunication Regulation and Municipal Access Agreements; Property Assessment &amp; Taxation Hearings and Litigation; Judicial Review and Statutory Appeals from Administrative Tribunals; Municipal Bylaws and Enforcement; Municipal Contracts; Labour and Employment; Privacy and Access to Information Issues; Municipal Liability and Defense Litigation; Environmental Law. More recently, Barry has concentrated his practice in Property Assessment and Taxation Litigation including appeals before the Composite Assessment Review Board (CARB) and Municipal Government Board (MGB); Judicial Review and Statutory Appeals from Administrative Tribunals; Annexation, Amalgamation and Inter-municipal Collaboration and Restructuring, Legislative Review and Drafting, and Municipal Governance and Authority.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h1></h1>'),
