(4714, 396, 'bio', 'Guy began his business practice in Vancouver, B.C., where, after some time in private practice, he acted as in house counsel to a publicly traded company. He has called Alberta home since 1992. He has dedicated his entire career to providing business law advice to local and international corporations, other forms of business organizations and municipal governments.\r\n\r\nHis practice now emphasizes on the areas of Business Acquisitions and Dispositions, ongoing Business Operational Matters and Succession Planning. Guy enjoys many long term client relationships where he has evolved with clients from start-up and rapid growth, through to maturity and stability and on to significant change. The nature of these activities requires close collaboration with a range of other professional advisors dedicated to the best interests of our clients, such as accounting, insurance and tax specialists.\r\n\r\nHe has earned the role of "trusted advisor" to many clients and Guy is often the first contact point to help determine the most appropriate course of action on business issues.'),
(4715, 396, '_bio', 'field_5323822abc024'),
(4716, 396, 'representative_work', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Counsel to international corporation with respect to all aspects of its business activities in Western Canada.</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance to widely held corporations in negotiating and completing business purchases by way of asset and share purchase transactions.</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance to vendors in negotiating and completing business sales by way of asset and share purchase transactions.</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance to closely held corporations and their shareholders to structure and implement effective Succession Planning strategies.</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance in helping establish new organizations for the purposes of encouraging regional economic development in Alberta.</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance to establish insurance reciprocals for the benefit of subscribers.</li>\r\n	<li>Counsel to large professional partnerships in relation to partnership expansion, business acquisition, tax planned reorganizations and Succession Planning.</li>\r\n	<li>Counsel to numerous private companies providing advice and direction in all aspects of business organization and operation including incorporations, amalgamations, reorganizations, financings, shareholders agreements, security of shareholder loans and Succession Planning.</li>\r\n	<li>Counsel to medical and dental professionals in relation to incorporation, organization and Succession Planning.</li>\r\n	<li>Counsel to cooperative based utility corporations in all aspects including statutory compliance, director and officer fiduciary duty and negotiating complex supply and distribution agreements.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
