(4921, 405, 'bio', '<div>\r\n\r\nTom practices primarily in the areas of Utility Regulation, Municipal and Administrative Law. He conducts litigation involving Municipalities and other public sector entities with respect to Professional Liability and Discipline. Tom has appeared before all levels of courts and tribunals, including numerous trials and appeals. He has over 20 years of experience and knowledge, which allows him to effectively represent his clients throughout Alberta, the Northwest Territories and the Yukon.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h1></h1>'),
(4922, 405, '_bio', 'field_5323822abc024'),
(4923, 405, 'representative_work', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Municipal Governance &amp; Authority: Throughout his career, Tom has provided advice and directions to Administrators and elected Officials of Municipalities with respect to the scope of their legislative authority and the options available to them. This has allowed Tom''s clients to more effectively achieve policy goals and objectives.</li>\r\n	<li>Expropriations: Tom has extensive experience in the area of expropriations and has acted on behalf of both expropriating authorities and expropriated landowners.</li>\r\n	<li>Utility Regulation: Tom has extensive experience representing the interests of Alberta municipal, residential, farm and small commercial customers of electricity and natural gas in proceedings before the Alberta Utilities Commission and its predecessor. Tom also acts for municipalities and other interested land owners in "facilities" applications before the Alberta Utilities Commission and Joint Panels considering the approval of large projects such as oil sands mines.</li>\r\n	<li>Administrative Law: Tom appears before or acts as counsel to numerous administrative tribunals. He also appears in the Court of Queen''s Bench and Court of Appeal on judicial reviews and appeals of decisions by such tribunals.</li>\r\n	<li>Professional Liability and Disciplinary Matters: Tom has extensive experience representing professionals in disciplinary proceedings before their governing Colleges including assisting in the preparation of responses to complaints, and the conduct of disciplinary hearings and appeals. He has also successfully defended professionals in lawsuits alleging failure to meet professional standards.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
