(6439, 472, 'bio', 'Bruce is a partner and has been practicing in Edmonton for the past 30 years. Bruce practices general corporate, commercial and real estate law with an emphasis on mergers, acquisitions and divestitures of businesses, corporate restructuring and reorganizations, commercial real estate, commercial leasing and financings. Bruce resolves business and corporate related issues for his clients using a multi-faceted approach that draws experience from a number of Business Law Groups within the firm. He has also extensive experience in the areas of shareholder agreements, joint ventures, franchising, corporate governance advisory work and drafting and negotiating commercial agreements.\r\n\r\nBruce has facilitated major projects including the acquisition, development, financing and leasing of high rise buildings, shopping centres, commercial buildings and residential subdivisions.'),
(6440, 472, '_bio', 'field_5323822abc024'),
(6441, 472, 'representative_work', 'Bruce''s attention to detail and efficiency allows him to offer his clients the comfort that the transaction will be completed to the highest standard possible and on a timely basis. Bruce resolves business and corporate issues in an expeditious and pragmatic basis. Bruce''s work includes:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Advice to national corporation activities in Alberta, assisting in the acquisition and development of land and leasing of retail premises.</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance to vendors and purchasers in negotiating and completing business asset and share sale transactions.</li>\r\n	<li>Assisting in the preparation and negotiation of required franchisee disclosure documentation and franchise agreements and related business matters to franchisors and franchisees.</li>\r\n	<li>Advising developers entering into and negotiating joint venture arrangements and agreements pertaining to acquisition and development of large scale commercial developments.</li>\r\n	<li>Counsel to numerous private companies providing advice and direction in all aspects of business organization and operation including incorporations, amalgamations, reorganizations, financings, shareholders agreements and security of shareholder loans.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCounsel to numerous home builders, buyers and sellers of residential real estate and providing advice on contracts, homeowners association and condominium issues.'),
