(6779, 507, 'ne_content', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Brownlee Welcomes 5 New Legal Professionals to the Team</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Brownlee LLP is Now Offering ADR Services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2014 Best Lawyer Awards</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>BROWNLEE LLP WOULD LIKE TO WELCOME THE FOLLOWING NEW MEMBERS TO OUR LEGAL TEAM</b>\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>David M. Pick, Partner</b>\r\n\r\nBrownlee is pleased to report that former Brownlee partner, David Pick, rejoined our partnership in the Calgary office on September 9th. Dave is well known to many of our clients and others in the insurance industry as an aggressive and efficient trial lawyer experienced in construction, fire, transportation, products liability, CGL and occupier issues, commercial disputes, coverage and auto matters. You can view David’s complete <a href="http://brownleelaw.com/edmonton?sobi2Task=sobi2Details&amp;catid=35&amp;sobi2Id=102">biography here.</a>\r\n\r\n<b>Jennifer A. Faircloth, Associate</b>\r\n\r\nJennifer Faircloth is welcomed by Brownlee LLP as part of their Litigation and Insurance Defence Team in their Calgary office. Jennifer received her Law Degree from the University of Manitoba and was called to the Manitoba Bar in 1999 followed by the Alberta Bar in 2004. Jennifer is member to several organizations including the Canadian Defence Lawyer, Defence Research Institute, the Canadian and Alberta Bar Associations and the Advocates Society. You can view Jennifer’s complete <a href="http://brownleelaw.com/calgary-lawyers?sobi2Task=sobi2Details&amp;catid=36&amp;sobi2Id=101">biography here.</a>\r\n\r\n<b>Nabeel Peermohamed, Associate</b>\r\n\r\nNabeel Peermohamed is welcomed by Brownlee LLP as part of their Litigation and Insurance Defence Team in their Calgary office. Nabeel received his Law Degree from the University of Calgary and was called to both the Alberta and British Columbia Bar in 2012. Nabeel is also a member of the Canada Tax Foundation. You can view Nabeel’s complete <a href="http://brownleelaw.com/calgary-lawyers?sobi2Task=sobi2Details&amp;catid=36&amp;sobi2Id=97">biography here.</a>\r\n\r\n<b>Charlotte A. St. Dennis, Associate</b>\r\n\r\nCharlotte A. St. Dennis is welcomed by Brownlee LLP as a part of their Municipal Department in their Edmonton office. Charlotte received her Law Degree from the University of Alberta and was called to the Alberta bar in 1986. Charlotte brings over 20 years of Municipal Law experience to Brownlee including strategic advice for municipal councils and extensive involvement in planning and development matters. You can view Charlotte’s complete <a href="http://brownleelaw.com/edmonton?sobi2Task=sobi2Details&amp;catid=35&amp;sobi2Id=103">biography here.</a>\r\n\r\n<b>J. Allison McDonald, Associate</b>\r\n\r\nBrownlee is pleased to announce the return of Allison McDonald who assumes lead of our Wills and Estate Planning group.  Allison is well known to most of our estates and trust clients and has extensive estate planning experience including the preparation of Family Trusts, Wills, Personal Directives and Enduring Powers of Attorney.  She also contributes significantly to our Succession Planning practice.  Allison has represented clients on a variety of estate matters including estate administration and contested estate matters.  You can view Allison’s complete <a href="http://brownleelaw.com/edmonton?sobi2Task=sobi2Details&amp;catid=35&amp;sobi2Id=104">biography here.</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>BROWNLEE LLP IS NOW OFFERING ADR SERVICES</b>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://brownleelaw.com/calgary-lawyers?sobi2Task=sobi2Details&amp;catid=36&amp;sobi2Id=68">Dennis K. Yasui, Q.C</a>. is now available to act as a mediator and arbitrator to assist in the resolution of civil disputes.  Dennis has 30 years of experience as a civil litigator and has represented clients in a wide variety of civil disputes.  This broad experience combined with his formal mediation training will offer clients a skilled and effective mediator or arbitrator.  Dennis will continue to practice in the firm’s Calgary Office.  You can view Dennis’s complete <a href="http://brownleelaw.com/calgary-lawyers?sobi2Task=sobi2Details&amp;catid=36&amp;sobi2Id=68">biography here.</a>\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>2014 BEST LAWYERS IN CANADA\r\n</b>\r\n\r\nThe Brownlee LLP Partnership would like to congratulate Allen R. Evaniew, Partner, Havelock B. Madill Q.C., Counsel, and Roger I. Swainson Q.C., Partner for the achievement of being named “2014’s Best Lawyers in Canada" in the following areas:\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://brownleelaw.com/edmonton?sobi2Task=sobi2Details&amp;catid=35&amp;sobi2Id=73"><b>Allen R. Evaniew</b></a>\r\n\r\nReal Estate Law\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://brownleelaw.com/edmonton?sobi2Task=sobi2Details&amp;catid=35&amp;sobi2Id=70"><b>Havelock B. Madill, Q.C.</b></a>\r\n\r\nCorporate and Commercial Litigation\r\n\r\nDirector and Officer Liability\r\n\r\nInsurance Law\r\n\r\nPersonal Injury Litigation\r\n\r\nProduct Liability Law\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://brownleelaw.com/edmonton?sobi2Task=sobi2Details&amp;catid=35&amp;sobi2Id=64"><b>Roger I. Swainson, Q.C.</b></a>\r\n\r\nReal Estate Law'),
