(7244, 579, '_ne_title', 'field_531fb61d778a4'),
(7245, 579, 'ne_content', 'The Minor Injury Regulation came into force in Alberta on October 1, 2004. The main effect of the regulation is to limit the amount of non-pecuniary damages that a motor vehicle accident victim may recover in respect of certain types of injuries. This limit, which is referred to as the soft-tissue injury cap, specifically applies to any injury which is determined to be a minor injury within the meaning of the Regulation.\r\n\r\n<a title="TMJ Injuries" href="http://localhost/brownlee-dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/TMJ-Injuries.pdf">View PDF Article</a><a href="http://localhost/brownlee-dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/TMJ-Injuries.pdf">\r\n</a>\r\n\r\nOctober 2011'),
