(7251, 581, 'ne_title', 'ALBERTA''S NEW SIGNIFICANT DELAY RULE: 2 YEARS AND YOU''RE OUT'),
(7252, 581, '_ne_title', 'field_531fb61d778a4'),
(7253, 581, 'ne_content', 'Prior to November of 2010, claims in Alberta were subject to a mandatory striking after 5 years of inactivity. That Rule rarely came into play. However, as of November, 2010, a claim that goes 2 years without a step that moves the matter to trial in a significant way will be vulnerable to being struck.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.brownleelaw.com/images/eBulletins/Strong_Defense/Delay%20Rule.pdf">View PDF Article</a>\r\n\r\nOctober 2011'),
