(7270, 584, '_ne_title', 'field_531fb61d778a4'),
(7271, 584, 'ne_content', 'The quantification of fatality claims involves the following types of awards:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Damages for bereavement, as set forth in the <em>Fatal Accidents Act</em>, R.S.A. 2000, c. F-8 ("<em>FAA</em>");</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Special damages for such things as funeral expenses and grief counseling, as set forth in the <em>FAA</em>;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Dependency loss; and</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Loss of valuable services.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href="http://localhost/brownlee-dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Fatal-Claims-calculation-of-damages.pdf">View PDF Article</a><a href="http://localhost/brownlee-dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Fatal-Claims-calculation-of-damages.pdf">\r\n</a>\r\n\r\nOctober 2012'),
