(7306, 592, '_ne_title', 'field_531fb61d778a4'),
(7307, 592, 'ne_content', 'We have been keeping our clients posted on this Rule. You may recall that it was set to come into effect on November 1, 2012, and was going to provide that a long delay application to strike the claim be warranted after a delay of 2 or more years since the last thing done to significantly advance the action towards trial. However, before it came into effect, the Legislature suspended the coming into effect date for a year to November 1, 2013, but left the 2 year delay portion of the rule in place.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/brownlee-dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/long-delay-rule-new.pdf">View PDF Article</a><a href="http://localhost/brownlee-dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/long-delay-rule-new.pdf">\r\n</a>\r\n\r\nSeptember 2013'),
