(7316, 594, 'ne_content', 'Sable Offshore Energy Inc. v. Ameron International Corp., 2013 SCC 37.\r\n\r\nAmeron International Corporation ("Ameron") and five other companies (collectively called "Amercoat") provided Sable Offshore Energy Inc. ("Sable) with paint for several buildings. Sable brought forth three lawsuits alleging that the paint failed to prevent corrosion against Ameron, Amercoat and 12 other contractors who prepared surfaces and applied the paint; the claims were for negligence, negligent misrepresentation and breach of a collateral warranty.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/brownlee-dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/pierringer.pdf">View PDF Article</a><a href="http://localhost/brownlee-dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/pierringer.pdf">\r\n</a>\r\n\r\nSeptember 2013'),
