(8715, 674, 'bio', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Assists clients with estate planning and related issues, including assessment of inter-provincial and international issues, insurance coverage and charitable donations.</li>\r\n	<li>Prepares Wills (including complex tax planned Wills containing spousal trusts, life insurance trusts, trusts for disabled beneficiaries and creditor proof trusts), Enduring Powers of Attorneys, Personal Directives, Codicils and Family Trusts.</li>\r\n	<li>Reviews and implements corporate structures and re-organization of family owned businesses including new incorporations, amalgamations, rollovers, wind-ups, Shareholder’s Agreements and Family Trusts to be used in these structures.</li>\r\n	<li>Prepares Applications for Grants of Probate and Resealing of Foreign Grants.</li>\r\n	<li>Works with legal counsel and other professionals both nationally and internationally to address the proper transfer of estate assets, including mines and minerals interests.</li>\r\n	<li>Works with Personal Representatives to assist them with the completion of the administration of the Estate, including addressing the transfer and sale of land, completion of the distributions to beneficiaries, and all other related Estate matters.</li>\r\n	<li>Provides advice to Trustees regarding trust administration issues.</li>\r\n	<li>Conducts Estate litigation matters including claims by and against Personal Representatives, beneficiaries, spouses and other interested parties.</li>\r\n	<li>Various experience acting for professionals in various representative capacities.</li>\r\n	<li>Experience acting for both sellers and buyers in transactional matters such as share and asset transactions.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
