(8751, 675, 'bio', 'John advises municipalities and other public sector clients on a broad range of corporate and commercial legal matters, with an emphasis on the structuring of the joint or inter-municipal provision of services by two or more parties. He has in-depth experience in advising on the optimum corporate structure for the providers and operators of services such as wireless broadband services, operation of water treatment plants, provision of water services, landfills and waste management operations, airport operations and other matters.\r\n\r\nJohn''s non-public sector experience includes acting for numerous clients in asset and share acquisitions and dispositions, amalgamations, pipeline acquisitions, commercial real estate acquisitions, dispositions, developments and leasing.\r\n\r\nHe also acts as corporate counsel for several non-profit and charitable institutions. This work includes the incorporation of the non-profit entity, establishment of governance framework, advising on corporate best practices and registration as a charity.\r\n\r\nJohn further acts as corporate counsel to First Nations for their business operations and governance matters. This has involved the tax-driven reorganization of their business operations into limited partnerships, acquisitions and dispositions of businesses and land and other matters.\r\n\r\nJohn has served on the City of St. Albert subdivision and development appeal board since 2008 and has acted as the Chairperson of that board since 2009. John has also served on the board of directors of a non-profit business incubator.'),
(8752, 675, '_bio', 'field_5323822abc024'),
(8753, 675, 'representative_work', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Establishment of corporate partnership framework for:</li>\r\n	<li>Large rural broadband wireless technology company with 18 founding partners;</li>\r\n	<li>First Canadian partnership of municipalities and First Nation to jointly own water utility services;</li>\r\n	<li>Creation of municipal utility corporation for 12 municipalities to jointly provide water utility services;</li>\r\n	<li>Creation of numerous municipal utility corporations for the provision of other utility services including water services, waste management services, airport operations;</li>\r\n	<li>Creation of regional services commissions for the joint municipal provision of utility services;</li>\r\n	<li>Creation of land trust for Alberta post-secondary institution for the development of their underutilized lands;</li>\r\n	<li>Creation of non-profit and charitable organizations;</li>\r\n	<li>Corporate counsel to many municipal utility corporations, housing authorities, regional services commissions;</li>\r\n	<li>Establishment of joint ventures between municipalities and private entities for the joint provision of: housing projects; operation of private forestry roads; landfill operations;</li>\r\n	<li>Corporate counsel to many non-profit and charitable organizations;</li>\r\n	<li>Counsel to municipalities and private parties on numerous commercial transactions;</li>\r\n	<li>Acquisition and disposition of shopping centres, office buildings, industrial warehouses;</li>\r\n	<li>Commercial leasing of shopping centres, office buildings, industrial warehouses.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
