(9687, 701, 'bio', 'For the past 30 years, Dennis’ practice has focused on civil litigation and advocacy but in a very wide variety of areas.  His practice currently focuses upon Alternative Dispute Resolution and in particular, the Mediation and Arbitration of civil disputes.\r\n\r\nDennis completed the intensive Divorce by Mediation course offered through the Legal Education Society of Alberta in 1990 and since then has acted a mediator in a variety of matters. More recently he has acted as an arbitrator in a land development matter.\r\n\r\nAs a litigator, Dennis’s practice has focused on complex matters which involve insurance coverage, commercial insurance defense, commercial contracts; defamation, negligent misrepresentation; commercial construction, oil and gas, professional liability, products liability, municipal liability; school liability including sexual abuse; commercial leases; shareholders disputes; water rights and access to water; development and planning, employment and labour, Human Rights and intellectual property.\r\n\r\nHe has had extensive experience advocating the interests of his clients in numerous forums including the Courts, administrative tribunals, arbitrations and mediations.  He has appeared before all levels of court in Alberta, the Supreme Court of British Columbia, the Supreme Court of the North West Territories, the Court of Queen’s Bench of Saskatchewan, the Court of Queen’s Bench of Manitoba, the Supreme Court of Canada (Leave Applications), the Environmental Appeal Board, The Alberta Human Rights Commission; the Board of Reference and the Waiver Committee of Alberta Health Services, the Board of Reference under the School Act  as well as other various arbitral tribunals.\r\n\r\nAlthough he is currently focusing on developing an Alternative Dispute Resolution Practice he will continue his Litigation practice and will continue to serve his many litigation clients.'),
(9688, 701, '_bio', 'field_5323822abc024'),
(9689, 701, 'representative_work', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Acts on behalf  of a number of insurers in defending architects, engineers, contractors and subcontractors  in faulty design and construction claims including numerous oil and gas facility and building envelope claims;</li>\r\n	<li>Acts on behalf of a number of insurers in defending claims and prosecuting subrogated claims arising from the catastrophic destruction of oil and gas equipment such as pipelines. processing plants and oil and gas rigs;</li>\r\n	<li>Acts on behalf of a number of municipalities in defending  a wide variety of claims including claims arising from the planning and development of land, breach of contract, breach of statutory duty, negligence including negligent misrepresentation;</li>\r\n	<li>Acts for a number of  insurers on a wide variety of coverage issues under All Risk Property Policies, Commercial General Liability Policies, Builders Risk Policies, and Professional Liability Policies;</li>\r\n	<li>Acts for various corporations and individuals in a wide variety of commercial disputes including disputes relating to shareholder rights and intellectual property rights;</li>\r\n	<li>Represents a variety of Public School Districts in a wide variety of claims including sexual abuse claims and complaints under the Alberta Human Rights Act;</li>\r\n	<li>Recently represented a School District before the Board of Reference in a 6 week hearing in respect of the dismissal of a teacher that resulted in a 600 page judgment in favour of our client.</li>\r\n	<li>Represented a municipality before the Waiver Committee of Alberta Health Services in an application for a waiver of the Nuisance and General Sanitation Regulation of the Public Health; and</li>\r\n	<li>Represented a municipality before the Environmental Appeal Board.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(9690, 701, '_representative_work', 'field_532382ccbc029'),
(9691, 701, 'memberships', 'Dennis is a member of the Law Society of Alberta, the Law Society of British Columbia, the ADR Institute of Alberta, The ADR Institute of Canada, the Canadian Bar Association, the Calgary Bar Association; the various CBA, Alberta Subsections; and the International Trade Mark Association.'),
(9692, 701, '_memberships', 'field_5323824dbc025'),
(9693, 701, 'presentations', 'Dennis has written and presented a number of papers on a wide variety of topics for the Canadian   Bar Association, Lexpert, The Canadian Institute, The Calgary Claims Managers Association and other industry groups.  The topics of his papers and presentations include Directors &amp; Officer’s Liability; Professional Liability Policies; Commercial General Liability Policies, Business Interruption Claims; the Limitations Act; Municipal Liability; Mediation; Good Faith Obligations of Insurers; Issues affecting Subrogation Rights; Conducting Jury Trials and the Quantification of Damages for Personal Injury Claims.'),
(9694, 701, '_presentations', 'field_532382fcbc02a'),
(9695, 701, 'publications', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Construction Claims and Alberta''s 10 Year Ultimate Limitation Period, Construction Business Magazine, 2012 (<a href="http://brownleelaw.com/images/Publications/Paper%20%20Construction%20Liitigation%20-%20Limitations%20Act%2009-21-2012%20C0419099.pdf">PDF</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>'),
