(9925, 709, 'new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'UTILITY REGULATION'),
(9926, 709, '_new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(9927, 709, 'new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'Brownlee''s extensive work with utilities throughout Alberta has provided its lawyers with a formidable depth of experience in the field of utility regulation.\r\n\r\nWe represent various intervenors (often ratepayers) in proceedings involving rates set by regulated utilities (electricity and natural gas) before the Alberta Utilities Commission. Brownlee has represented various types of ratepayers, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>municipalities</li>\r\n	<li>homeowners</li>\r\n	<li>farm owners</li>\r\n	<li>small commercial customers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition to financial concerns, ratepayer concerns can include environmental and socioeconomic issues, among others. Brownlee understands the various and dynamic concerns that often arise in utilities law and are able to capably advance the interests of clients, regardless of their form. It is the goal of our Utility Regulation practice group to satisfy the objective of our clients in a way that is proactive, timely, and practical.'),
(9928, 709, '_new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(9929, 709, 'new_paragraph_1_new_title', 'FACILITIES APPLICATIONS'),
(9930, 709, '_new_paragraph_1_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(9931, 709, 'new_paragraph_1_new_content', 'Brownlee also acts for municipalities and other interested landowners in "facilities" applications before the Alberta Utilities Commission and Joint Panels considering the approval of large projects such as oil sands mines.'),
(9932, 709, '_new_paragraph_1_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(9933, 709, 'new_paragraph', '2'),
(9934, 709, '_new_paragraph', 'field_531d56646e418'),
(9935, 710, '_edit_last', '1'),
(9936, 710, '_edit_lock', '1395268463:1'),
(9937, 710, 'new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'TRUSTS'),
(9938, 710, '_new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(9939, 710, 'new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'Brownlee understands that owners and individuals alike may need to plan for the managed transfer of property to others. Brownlee works with both types of clients, usually in the areas of estate planning and succession planning, to determine whether or not the creation of a trust is in the client''s or their beneficiaries best interest. We are aware that there are various reasons why a trust would benefit a client and have experience creating trusts that effectively serve a vast selection of diverse and unique needs. From the exceedingly complex to the refreshingly simple, Brownlee can capably establish trusts of all kinds.\r\n\r\nOur clients are often referred to us by various professionals who are knowledgeable of Brownlee''s capacity in the area of trust creation. We often work in collaboration with or receive referrals from:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>accountants</li>\r\n	<li>financial planners</li>\r\n	<li>investment managers</li>\r\n	<li>insurance agents</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOnce Brownlee determines that a trust is the most beneficial option available to a client, our dedicated practitioners will capably establish a trust that is manageable, efficient, and delivers the expected value. It is Brownlee''s goal to establish trusts only when they can reasonably and effectively serve the interests of our clients.'),
(9940, 710, '_new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(9941, 710, 'new_paragraph', '1'),
