(10321, 738, 'new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'Corporate Practice'),
(10322, 738, '_new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10323, 738, 'new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'The Brownlee LLP Corporate Practice Group provides advice to our business clients in all phases from initial startup to the implementation of significant change and, where appropriate, sale, winding-up or dissolution. We have a broad spectrum of expertise to address the specific circumstances of our clients at the various phases of their business. At any given time, any one or more of the following examples may be relevant to your business:'),
(10324, 738, '_new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10325, 738, 'new_paragraph_1_new_title', 'Establishment'),
(10326, 738, '_new_paragraph_1_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10327, 738, 'new_paragraph_1_new_content', 'In startup, clients will need to select the form of business vehicle most appropriate for operations. Many will choose a business corporation, but realistic and viable alternatives should be carefully considered in order that an informed decision can be made.'),
(10328, 738, '_new_paragraph_1_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10329, 738, 'new_paragraph_2_new_title', 'Ownership and Governance'),
(10330, 738, '_new_paragraph_2_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10331, 738, 'new_paragraph_2_new_content', 'In addition to determining the original owners of a business, thought should be given as to how owners can be added (such as key employees) and how they can depart or be removed. Mechanisms can be designed to accommodate how and when these changes can occur in a manner appropriate to the relevant circumstances. Further, guidelines are important to help establish the policy and direction for a business and facilitate implementation of top level decisions. Specific rights or limitations may be required in governing documents. Many times a shareholder agreement, partnership agreement or some other relationship document will be recommended.'),
(10332, 738, '_new_paragraph_2_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10333, 738, 'new_paragraph_3_new_title', 'Finance'),
(10334, 738, '_new_paragraph_3_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10335, 738, 'new_paragraph_3_new_content', 'Initial investment and additional funds that can be made available for the capital and operational needs of a business are considered closely with our clients and their financial advisors. When the necessary decisions are made, they can be supported with the appropriate agreements to facilitate the relevant funding arrangements.'),
(10336, 738, '_new_paragraph_3_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10337, 738, 'new_paragraph_4_new_title', 'Ongoing Operations'),
(10338, 738, '_new_paragraph_4_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10339, 738, 'new_paragraph_4_new_content', 'Brownlee LLP advises on the wide range of issues facing owners and management directed at the successful functioning of the business and the workplace. The following are examples of some common issues:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>organization policy and direction;</li>\r\n	<li>discharge of fiduciary duty of directors and officers;</li>\r\n	<li>management empowerment and control;</li>\r\n	<li>directors meetings and minutes;</li>\r\n	<li>owner and third party financial support;</li>\r\n	<li>routine annual corporate compliance;</li>\r\n	<li>financial records and disclosure;</li>\r\n	<li>employment and labour;</li>\r\n	<li>intellectual property;</li>\r\n	<li>risk management;</li>\r\n	<li>annual shareholder meetings;</li>\r\n	<li>securities compliance and disclosure;</li>\r\n	<li>distribution of profits; and</li>\r\n	<li>dealing with unexpected circumstances when they arise.</li>\r\n</ol>'),
(10340, 738, '_new_paragraph_4_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10341, 738, 'new_paragraph_5_new_title', 'Purchase or Sale of a Business and Succession Planning'),
(10342, 738, '_new_paragraph_5_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10343, 738, 'new_paragraph_5_new_content', 'A business may be faced with a voluntary or involuntary change in ownership and control. Where our client is proceeding with a merger or acquisition, the appropriate business vehicle must be designed to accommodate the long term goals following completion of the transaction. In circumstances where our client controls the subject business, an opportunity for smooth transfer or succession planning can arise. In all situations where significant ownership changes are likely, we collaborate closely with our clients and their other professionals including financial, accounting and tax advisors to help achieve the objectives of our clients in the relevant circumstances.'),
(10344, 738, '_new_paragraph_5_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10345, 738, 'new_paragraph_6_new_title', 'Ongoing Communications'),
(10346, 738, '_new_paragraph_6_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10347, 738, 'new_paragraph_6_new_content', 'Our Brownlee LLP Corporate Practice Group encourages regular open and frank discussions with our clients in order to best identify the most important considerations and to respond appropriately to the needs of our clients.'),
(10348, 738, '_new_paragraph_6_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10349, 738, 'new_paragraph', '7'),
(10350, 738, '_new_paragraph', 'field_531d56646e418'),
(10351, 739, '_edit_last', '1'),
(10352, 739, '_edit_lock', '1395259104:1'),
(10353, 739, 'new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'Contested Estates'),
(10354, 739, '_new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10355, 739, 'new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'While Brownlee LLP encourages the creation of clear estate transfer plans to mitigate the risk of disputes occurring following death. We also help executors and administrators of estates, as well as beneficiaries, when estate planning has either not been done or was done poorly. Our experienced Contested Estates practice group understands that conflicts arising from improper estate planning can carry a strong emotional and psychological component. Brownlee''s primary objective is to satisfy our clients'' goals in a way that minimizes stress and conflict. Brownlee strives to provide all its Contested Estate clients with the best possible outcome on a timely basis to they can move forward with their lives.\r\n\r\nWe advise our clients when:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>no will exists and Alberta''s Intestate Legislation applies</li>\r\n	<li>existing wills have not properly provided for family members or are otherwise open to challenge</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBrownlee advocates mediation and collaborative approaches to help beneficiaries resolve issues quickly and without undue conflict. Approaches of this kind are far easier to put into place when our Estate Planning Team is involved in disputes at an early stage. It is in our clients'' best interest to contact us immediately following the development of conflicts or when conflicts are expect to arise within an estate to better facilitate a fair and just resolution. Brownlee understands that there are instances when all other avenues of settlement have been exhausted and it is necessary to proceed to trial. Fortunately, Brownlee''s capable Contested Estates practice group is experienced in arguing matters of this nature before the courts. Brownlee is capable and willing to pursue litigation if such an approach is necessary to protect and further the rights of our clients.'),
(10356, 739, '_new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10357, 739, 'new_paragraph', '1'),
(10358, 739, '_new_paragraph', 'field_531d56646e418'),
(10359, 740, '_edit_last', '1'),
(10360, 740, '_edit_lock', '1395259132:1'),
(10361, 740, 'new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'Construction Litigation, Bond Claims, & Builders Lien Litigation'),
(10362, 740, '_new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10363, 740, 'new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'Brownlee LLP is constantly expanding its already comprehensive expertise in the area of construction litigation, bond claims and builders'' lien litigation. The skilled practitioners at Brownlee understand the brick-and-mortar processes that are required for the successful construction of a project, and by applying this knowledge, can capably pursue litigation on behalf of clients who are dealing with issues that arise as a result of deficient construction or non-payment of monies owed. Brownlee has built a respected practice representing all stakeholders in the construction industry in disputes arising from:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mis-steps, real or perceived, that occurred during the procurement process</li>\r\n	<li>A variety of issues that occur during construction of a project</li>\r\n	<li>Disputes regarding contractual obligations including construction defaults, insolvencies, bond claims and builders'' liens</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBrownlee clients come from every aspect of the construction industry and include the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Project owners</li>\r\n	<li>General contractors and subcontractors</li>\r\n	<li>Insurers</li>\r\n	<li>Government departments and organizations</li>\r\n	<li>Non-profit organizations</li>\r\n	<li>Engineers</li>\r\n	<li>Architects</li>\r\n	<li>Planners</li>\r\n	<li>Interior designers</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(10364, 740, '_new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10365, 740, 'new_paragraph_1_new_title', 'Advisory Services'),
(10366, 740, '_new_paragraph_1_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10367, 740, 'new_paragraph_1_new_content', 'In addition to our understanding of the physical processes of construction, we also have significant expertise in construction contract, surety law and builders'' liens, and can thoroughly advise clients in regard to their contractual and statutory obligations as well as provide strategic advice in respect of the efficient and effective resolution of any disputes. Brownlee''s proactive approach to risk management, coupled with extensive experience in construction litigation, helps our clients avoid unnecessary disputes, builders'' liens, and other costly claims that can otherwise occur. For clients actively involved in construction, Brownlee acts in an advisory role to make certain that our clients respect all relevant rules and legislation, and in particular:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ensure public sector owners comply with interprovincial trade agreements such as the Agreement on Internal Trade and the New West Partnership Trade Agreement</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure both public and private sector clients follow procurement law</li>\r\n	<li>Advise clients on their contractual rights and obligations</li>\r\n	<li>Advise clients on their payment obligations so as to avoid claims and subsequent disputes</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(10368, 740, '_new_paragraph_1_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10369, 740, 'new_paragraph', '2'),
(10370, 740, '_new_paragraph', 'field_531d56646e418'),
(10371, 741, '_edit_last', '1'),
(10372, 741, '_edit_lock', '1395259186:1'),
(10373, 741, 'new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'Contract Drafting and Review'),
(10374, 741, '_new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10375, 741, 'new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'Brownlee advises all stakeholders in construction projects on best practices in contract drafting and review with the goal of preventing construction disputes as projects move forward. We provide or assist with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Drafting and review of procurement documents (e.g., Request for Qualifications and Expressions of Interest, Request For Proposals, Tender Calls)</li>\r\n	<li>Drafting and review of construction contracts (e.g., Lump Sum, Construction Management, Design Build Contracts)</li>\r\n	<li>Architectural, Engineering and Consulting agreements</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(10376, 741, '_new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10377, 741, 'new_paragraph_1_new_title', 'Project Monitoring and Review'),
(10378, 741, '_new_paragraph_1_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10379, 741, 'new_paragraph_1_new_content', 'Brownlee stands ready to advise our clients at any stage of a construction project. We review and advise on:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The conduct and monitoring of competitive procurement processes</li>\r\n	<li>Competitive procurement liability claims and litigation (e.g., compliance with procurement processes, compliance with fairness principles)</li>\r\n	<li>The progress and monitoring of construction projects</li>\r\n	<li>The supervision, monitoring and management of consulting services</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(10380, 741, '_new_paragraph_1_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10381, 741, 'new_paragraph_2_new_title', 'Risk Management'),
(10382, 741, '_new_paragraph_2_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10383, 741, 'new_paragraph_2_new_content', 'Brownlee''s considerable knowledge of procurement and construction law helps our clients keep their projects on track. We provide:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Checks to ensure compliance with agreements such as the Agreement on Internal Trade, the New West Partnership Trade Agreement</li>\r\n	<li>Analysis of whether procurement processes and decisions comply with procurement law</li>\r\n	<li>Assessment of any related risks</li>\r\n	<li>Analysis of existing procurement policies and guidelines, and development of new policies and guidelines where necessary</li>\r\n	<li>Advice on best practices in managing construction contracts</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(10384, 741, '_new_paragraph_2_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10385, 741, 'new_paragraph_3_new_title', 'Clients'),
(10386, 741, '_new_paragraph_3_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(10387, 741, 'new_paragraph_3_new_content', 'Our construction and procurement law clients include all stakeholders in the construction industry, such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Project owners</li>\r\n	<li>General contractors and subcontractors</li>\r\n	<li>Insurers</li>\r\n	<li>Government departments and organizations</li>\r\n	<li>Non-profit organizations</li>\r\n	<li>Engineers</li>\r\n	<li>Architects</li>\r\n	<li>Planners</li>\r\n	<li>Interior designers</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(10388, 741, '_new_paragraph_3_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(10389, 741, 'new_paragraph', '4'),
