(11124, 779, '_new_paragraph_4_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(11125, 779, 'new_paragraph_4_new_content', 'In recent years, Alberta has seen the introduction of entirely new <i>Rules of Court</i>, the introduction of the<i>Minor Injury Regulations</i> Cap<i> </i>and significant changes to the <i>Insurance Act</i>, including those limiting the vicarious liability of rental agencies.  The legal terrain upon which insurance and other litigated disputes are decided is ever changing. As Alberta’s preeminent firm of trial lawyers, Brownlee LLP launched the “Strong Defence” Bulletin  to help keep our clients up to date with practical and succinct reports on developments that may affect your business, your risk management analysis and your litigation strategies.  Through our connections to Canadian Litigation Counsel and Harmonie Group (a network of trial lawyers covering every Province and state in North America and many other countries beyond) we are uniquely positioned to service the needs of our multi-national clients and keep them informed.'),
