(11141, 782, 'new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'Firm Profile'),
(11142, 782, '_new_paragraph_0_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(11143, 782, 'new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'Brownlee LLP is a mid-sized, regional law firm with offices in Calgary and Edmonton, providing the breadth and depth of service of a full-service law firm throughout Alberta and the Yukon, Nunavut and Northwest Territories. With extensive and long-standing practices in almost all legal disciplines, Civil Litigation, Municipal and Administrative Law, and Corporate-Commercial Law remain the cornerstones and core strengths upon which we continue to build extensive specialized and unique practice areas.\r\nOur firm was founded in the late 1930''s by the late John E. Brownlee, the 5th Premier of Alberta, who was the original architect of a client-centered service focused on local issues important to the client wherever they are located across this Province and the Territories. These traditions continue to this day, which in turn provide for a constant stimulus for innovation in response to the needs of our clients, and issues and adversities that they may face. The firm now draws upon the skills and expertise of its many dedicated practice groups which have arisen and been created in response to our clients'' requirements. Working within these teams, and on a broader level as a firm built upon common history, purpose and principles, we service the extremely broad and diverse nature of legal services required by our clients and the diverse economic landscape of Alberta. Today, this unique approach to legal services has served to make Brownlee LLP a very trusted and recognizable name throughout Western Canada.'),
(11144, 782, '_new_paragraph_0_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
